what mine did was basically run into a ton of BRK, cause that's very likely, which gets the stack pointer to eventually wrap into ROM which once an interrupt happens means that the stack is suddenly read only and no return addresses are actually written :)
so then the return address is whereever the stack pointer happens to point to when the interrupt happened
whoknows! i just trial and error'd it until it works because literally any branch that's taken or not taken on that frame vastly changes where you end up
